ODE XXIV. ,

Tms Ode is of the same class, and was probably written about the same time as the early ones of the third book, i. e. about A. n. c. 728. It deals with the licentious abuses of the times, and points indirectly to Augustus as the real reformer of them, as in the second Ode of the first book. The variety of images and illustrations in this Ode is very remarkable, and they are particu- larly well choscn and original.
